content:
OUT! TIMBER! Adil Rashid wraps this up. Wrong 'un around middle and off, Alzarri Joseph strides out in front and goes for the drive. Not getting to the pitch of it meant a massive gap between the bat and ball, and the ball has sneaked past the gate into the stumps. England has won the first ODI by a mammoth margin of 238 runs.
Alzarri Joseph b A Rashid 12 (19b 1x4 0x6)
Floated on middle and leg, Alzarri Joseph gets it clipped off the pads to leg slip.
Full and on the pads, Jayden Seales goes for the flick but misses. Wears it on his pads for nothing.
Good length around off, Jayden Seales swings and misses.
FOUR! A boundary down the ground, and Seales has now moved to 29 in the blink of an eye. On a length around middle and leg, Jayden Seales hammers this down to the long on fence for four.
Good length on the pads, Alzarri Joseph flicks this over forward square leg for one.
Back of a length on the pads, Jayden Seales tickles this to square leg for one.
Good length on off, Jayden Seales gets it edged onto his pads for no run.
Wrong'un on the pads, Alzarri Joseph swings and misses. The first slip fielder catches this but the appeal goes in vain as the batter has not hit this with his bat.
Short around off, Jayden Seales punches this to sweeper cover for one.
FOUR! Full toss on the pads, Jayden Seales sweeps this towards the vacant deep square leg region for four runs.
SIX! Identical hits for sixes. This was tossed up on the pads again, and Seales has slogged this over the fence towards long on region for six more.
SIX! Tossed up, closer to the batter. Jayden Seales clears his front foot and slogs this up and over the long on fence for a biggie.
Full and wide of off, Jayden Seales swings and misses.
Short-pitched again, around middle and off. Alzarri Joseph sits under it.
Short-pitched, around off. Alzarri Joseph ducks down.
FOUR! Short-pitched, around middle and leg, Alzarri Joseph pulls this through backward square leg region for a boundary.
On a length around middle and off, Alzarri Joseph flicks this over mid-wicket for two.
Short-pitched, around leg. Alzarri Joseph ducks down.
Back of a length on off, Alzarri Joseph defends this off his back foot.
Full and on the pads, Jayden Seales rolls this to mid on for no run.
SIX! Something to cheer for the Windies supporters. Tossed up on the pads, Jayden Seales clears his front foot and slogs this up and over the fence towards deep mid-wicket region for six.
Nudged towards square leg for one more.
Tossed up on the pads, Jayden Seales tucks this to short fine for one.
Full and on the pads, Alzarri Joseph flicks this to mid-wicket for one.
Wrong'un around middle and leg, Alzarri Joseph goes for the wild heave but gets it off the inside of his bat towards short fine for no run.
Back of a length around middle and leg, Jayden Seales misses the flick and gets it clipped off the pads towards short leg for no run.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Slower one, angling away from the batter. Gudakesh Motie clears his front foot again and looks to take on the fielders inside the circle on the off-side. The ball miscues off the cue end and hangs over the English skipper Harry Brook at extra cover. Brook settles underneath and holds onto this. Also, Jayden Seales is the last batter in for the Windies!
Gudakesh Motie c H Brook b J Overton 18 (11b 3x4 1x6)
Short-pitched, around off, Gudakesh Motie clears his front foot and swings hard at it but misses.
Short-pitched, around off, Alzarri Joseph looks to drop this down but gets it gloved wide to the right of the keeper for one.
Back of a length around off, Alzarri Joseph leaves this one too.
Short-pitched, around middle and leg. Alzarri Joseph ducks down.
Wrong'un around the pads, Motie rocks back and jams this out.
FOUR! Fuller on the pads, Gudakesh Motie gets down on a knee and paddles this towards the fine leg region for four runs.
WIDE! Full and wide outside off, Gudakesh Motie leaves it.

SIX! Hammered away for a biggie now. It is kind of open nets for Motie and he is making the most of it. Fuller around middle and off, Gudakesh Motie lofts this up and over the fence towards long off for a biggie.
Quicker one around middle and leg, Gudakesh Motie tucks this to mid-wicket for no run.
FOUR! Driven away for four. Tossed up wide outside off, Gudakesh Motie strides to the pitch of the ball and drives this past a diving wide mid off for four runs.
Floated around the pads, Alzarri Joseph tucks this through mid-wicket for one.
BEATEN! Full again and outside off as well, Gudakesh Motie looks to drive it again, on the up but gets beaten on the outside edge this time.
FOUR! Fine shot! Much fuller and in that channel outside off, Gudakesh Motie leans on and drives it through the gap towards mid off for a boundary.
Another back of a length delivery, around leg, Gudakesh Motie misses his tickle shot and gets hit on the thighpad.
Back of a length and a bit outside off, Alzarri Joseph runs it down to deep third for a single.
On a length and around middle, Alzarri Joseph nudges it towards mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! West Indies lose their eighth and Matthew Forde is gone, as Jamie Overton picks up his second! Short of a length and around the right shoulder of the batter, Matthew Forde goes back and looks to pull it. But the ball gets big on him and it takes the top edge of the bat and goes towards deep third man. Saqib Mahmood runs in forward there and takes this catch around his face.
Matthew Forde c S Mahmood b J Overton 1 (3b 0x4 0x6)
Nagging length and around off, Motie defends it off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! GONE! ANOTHER CATCH FOR ENGLISH SKIPPER! Touch short and around off, Amir Jangoo goes back, crouches and swipes it hard. The ball goes off the middle of the bat but towards mid-wicket, where Harry Brook flies to his left and takes another stunner. Windies lose their seventh and they are just on the verge of a big defeat!
Amir Jangoo c H Brook b A Rashid 14 (25b 0x4 0x6)
Tempting length and slower through the air, Amir Jangoo goes back and swipes it to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Tossed it up and on the pads, Jangoo clips it towards square leg.
Much shorter and around off, Amir Jangoo backs away and punches it but straight back to the bowler.
A googly, on a length and around off, Amir Jangoo plays out to the leg side off the back foot.
Back of a length and angling into the body of the batter, Matthew Forde lifts his front leg and looks to swipe it but misses and gets hit on his belly.
Hard length and around off, Jangoo drops it down towards extra cover for a quick single. Also, 100 comes up for Windies!
Lands it fuller again and around middle, Matthew Forde uses his feet and heaves it his shot off the inner half of the bat to deep mid-wicket for a single to get off the mark.
WIDE! Fuller but down the leg side, Forde misses his flick shot and it is called a wide.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another batter perished and the Windies lose their sixth! Short of a length again and around the right shoulder of the batter, Roston Chase goes back and looks to pull it. That previous delivery was still going through his mind as Jamie Overton had set him up very nicely here. The ball gets big on Chase, and he mistimes his shot towards deep square leg, where Will Jacks makes no mistake.
Roston Chase c W Jacks b J Overton 9 (13b 1x4 0x6)
OUCH! Short of a length, around off, gets an extra bounce off the deck, Roston Chase gets cramped up for room, and he looks to defend it, but the ball hits him on his gloves and goes towards point.
Hard length and angling into the body of the batter, Chase plays out off the back foot to square leg.
Nagging length and on the pads, Chase flicks it off the back foot to deep square leg for one.
A googly, very full and around off, Jangoo uses his feet and drives it through covers for a single.
Slower through the air, full and outside off, Chase waits and pats it down towards cover point for one.
Drops it a bit short again and outside off as well, Jangoo reaches out and cuts it to deep point for a single.
A googly, on a tempting length and around middle, Chase turns it towards square leg and takes a quick single.
Begins with a loosener, short and outside off, Jangoo cuts it through covers for a single.
Hits the hard length and around off, Jangoo cuts it through covers for a single.
On a good length and outside off, Amir Jangoo looks to play out to the off side but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and outside off, Roston Chase mistimes his lofted shot but it falls down in the vacant cover point region. They take a single.
WIDE! Short and down the leg side, Chase doesn't offer any shot at it. Called a wide!

An appeal for caught behind, but the umpire shakes his head! Harry Brook has instantly reviewed this! Back of a length and down the leg side, Roston Chase presses back, lifts his front leg up and looks to swipe it across and seems to have got an inside edge on its way to the keeper. UltraEdge shows that it has clipped his shirt, and Brook loses the review!
On a length and around off, Roston Chase shows the full face of the bat to defend it back to the bowler.

Jamie Overton is back into the attack and starts off with a full ball, outside off, Amir Jangoo drives it through covers. Will Jacks runs in to his left in the deep and puts in a slide to save one run for his side.
FOUR! A boundary amidst the chaos for Windies! Too short and around middle, Roston Chase goes back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tempting length and around off, Chase uses his feet and drills it back to the bowler.
Nagging length and around off, Roston Chase blocks it off.
Tossed it up and around off, Jangoo comes forward and drives it through covers for one more.
Short and around off, Roston Chase punches it through covers for one to get off the mark.

OUT! CAUGHT! ANOTHER BRILLIANT CATCH! West Indies are getting folded here as they lose their half of the side! Dragged length and a bit outside off, gets it to turn away from the batter. Jewel Andrew goes back and looks to cut it at first. But he gets deceived by the turn and ends up chipping it aerially towards cover. The English skipper, Harry Brook, flies to his left there and takes this stunning catch with both his hands.
Jewel Andrew c H Brook b J Bethell 8 (7b 0x4 1x6)
WIDE! Drifting it down the leg side, Jewel Andrew misses his sweep shot. Called a wide. A distracting appeal for caught behind to save the wide!
Switches to around the wicket and bowls it a bit fuller, around middle, Amir Jangoo takes out his front leg forward and flicks it to square leg.
WIDE! Full but down the leg side, Amir Jangoo has a swing at it but misses. Called a wide!
Lands it fuller again and around middle, Amir nudges it to mid-wicket.
Full and a bit outside off, Jangoo drills it back to the bowler.

Just short! Back of a length and around leg, Amir Jangoo swivels and looks to pull it. But gets it off the handle of the bat, and the ball goes, but falls down just ahead of the diving leg slip fielder.
On a dragged length and attacks the stumps, Amir defends it off the back foot into the pitch.
On a good length and around off, Amir keeps it out to the off side.
Nagging length and around middle, Jewel blocks it off back to the bowler.
SIX! ALL THE WAY! Floated it up, around off, Jewel Andrew clears out his front leg away a bit, and hits it from his arc with a slog. The ball sails over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Quicker and short, around off, Andrew defends it off the back foot.
Dragged length and outside off, Amir plays out to the off side for a single.
Tempting length and around off, Jangoo defends it to the off side.
Tossed it up and outside off, Amir Jangoo goes across and on his knees to sweep but misses.

Again a massive appeal, but this time for LBW and the umpire shakes his head again! On a good length and around middle, Amir Jangoo shuffles across and looks to flick it across but misses and gets pinged on the front pad. Probably, it will be going over the stumps!
On a hard length and around off, Jangoo drops it down towards cover.
Short and around middle, Jangoo pulls it down towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.

WIDE! Hard length and down the leg side, Amir Jangoo hops back and looks to tickle it fine, but gets beaten on the inside edge on its way to the keeper. There is a loud appeal for caught behind, but the umpire is unmoved. The keeper, Jos Buttler, is too interested, and England are going upstairs! There is nothing on UltraEdge, and England lose their review!

OUT! CAUGHT! CARSE HAS PLUCKED A STUNNER! Short of a length and angling into the body of the batter, particularly around the head of Shai Hope as he goes back and looks to pull it. He closes his eyes off the ball and ends up hitting it off the upper half of the bat. The ball goes very fast and flat towards deep backward square leg, where Brydon Carse comes in running to his left. He sees the ball going over the head and just stretches his body out of the motion backwards. In the end, he extends his left arm to take this stunner. What a grab!
Shai Hope (c) c B Carse b S Mahmood 25 (21b 4x4 0x6)
Full and around off, seaming in, Shai drives it to mid off from the front foot. This is some effort bowling from Saqib!
On a good length and around off, Shai Hope pats it down towards cover point. Also, Jamie Overton is back on the field, a good news for the English camp.
Back of a length, around off, Hops rides the bounce and drops it down to the left of cover for a quick single.
Short of a length and around off, Hope lofts it over mid off and takes two runs. It hasn't come off the middle of the bat but gets enough to clear the fielder there.
FOUR! Shot of confidence! Again on the back of a length and a touch outside off, Shai Hope hops up and cuts it over the cover point fielder for a boundary.
Hits the hard length and around off, Shai turns it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length and around off, Jewel opens his bat face off late and runs it down to deep third for a single.
Much fuller and around off, tails back in, Jewel Andrew manages to bring his bat down and jams it out to mid off.
Length and outside off, Hope punches it to cover.

FOUR! Saqib Mahmood almost had another wicket. Hand on face moments for England. Extra effort from Saqib Mahmood as he bowls it on a length and around off, on top of off. Hope looks to defend but is well beaten, gets an inside edge and it goes past the stumps to fine leg for a boundary.
Short of a good length and around off, Hope blocks. Solid from Saqib Mahmood.
Andrew is underway! Good length delivery, outside off, Andrew drops it to third man for a single.

OUT! GONE! The man in form goes! Keacy Carty was coming off back-to-back centuries against Ireland! He was the key to this chase! Saqib Mahmood induces the false shot! Bowls the hard length and around off, extra bounce and Keacy Carty looks to hoick it but slices his shot to mid off, where Harry Brook takes a sitter.
Keacy Carty c H Brook b S Mahmood 22 (26b 3x4 0x6)
A length ball, around off, nips back in sharply. Hope looks to push it away but inside edges it past the stumps and to fine leg for one.
Two to end the over! Touch fuller and on middle, Keacy Carty looks to heave but closes the bat face too early, it goes high and well above mid-wicket for a couple.
Tails one back in from the length on middle, Keacy Carty nudges it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, short of a length. Keacy Carty punches it firmly but straight to point.
A gentle full toss, outside off. Hope knocks it to mid off. Harry Brook dives to his right and saves a certain boundary. Just a run.
SWING AND A MISS! It was there to be hit! Short in length and wide outside off. Hope swings across but misses.
Pushes it very full and angling around off, Hope punches it to cover.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over. Bowls it quicker and on middle, Keacy Carty lofts it over mid on and mid-wicket for a boundary. West Indies need more and more.

Floats it full and on middle and leg. Keacy Carty chips it to the right of the bowler. Jacob Bethell dives but fails to stop. Keacy Carty wants a quick single but is sent from the halfway mark. Gets back easily.
This is full and on middle, Keacy Carty nudges it to square leg.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Keacy Carty sweeps it to short fine leg.

CHANCE! That came quickly! Jamie Overton does not even stop in his follow-through, as he tries to take on his right side but gets hit on the webbing between the thumb and the first finger. He keeps on running in pain and makes his way to the dugout. Touch fuller and on middle, Keacy Carty chips it back to Jamie Overton, who tries to take it with his right hand but fails to hold on. Hopefully, he is fine. Jacob Bethell to finish the over.
Jamie Overton bowls it on a length and on middle, Hope turns it in front of mid-wicket and calls for a quick single.
FOUR! West Indies building a nice partnership here! Fine shot from the man in form! Shorter and outside off. Keacy Carty pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short in length and on middle, Keacy Carty nudges it to square leg.
OFF THE TOE END! Bowls into the surface, slightly short. Keacy Carty looks to loft it away but cue ends it over mid off for a brace.
On a nagging length and around off, extra bounce and pace on this one. Keacy Carty is taken by surprise as he defends this one.
A length ball on top of off. Keacy Carty tries to play with an angled bat but it rolls to the keeper.
Serves it full and outside off, Keacy Carty strokes it straight to cover.
12 runs off the over. Just the over West Indies were looking to break the shackles! Fuller ball on middle, Keacy Carty taps it on the leg side for one.
Length and outside off, Hope knocks it to cover for a single.
FOUR! First shot that a batter will actually like! Proper cricketing shot! On a good length and on middle and leg, Hope punches with a straight bat past the bowler and it races to the fence.
Drags his length back and angles it on the pads. Hope looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! The skipper is showing some intent! This is full and outside off. Hope leans across and drives but gets a thick outside edge over the slip cordon and past third man for four runs.
Brydon Carse bowls into the blockhole, around off. Hope jams it out nicely past covers for a couple more.
Length ball on middle, Keacy Carty nudges it to mid-wicket.
Short in length and around off, Keacy Carty taps it in the region at short third man. They cross, the throw comes and goes past the keeper's stumps and they take one more.
FOUR! He is the man West Indies will look over in this chase! Bowls it full and outside off. Keacy Carty punches it square on the off side for a boundary.
On a nagging length and around off, jags back in sharply. Keacy Carty hangs back and blocks.
Well outside off, shorter and Keacy Carty leaves it alone.
Pushes it full and close to the off pole. Keacy Carty awkwardly pushes it through cover-point for a couple of runs.
Wide! Serves it full and down the leg side. Keacy Carty fails to clip it away.
Brydon Carse shapes in a full ball on middle, Hope digs it out to cover.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Both the openers are gone in two overs. This is Test match stuff from Carse! A good length ball, around off, it lands and straightens off the surface. Brandon King is squared up as he goes back to defend but gets a thin outside edge to the keeper, Jos Buttler, who takes it. West Indies in trouble!
Brandon King c J Buttler b B Carse 10 (14b 1x4 0x6)
Short of a length and outside off, swings away. King has a feel for it, puts his bat on it but misses.
This is full and outside off, Keacy Carty splices his drive to third man for a single.
A bumper, around off at 136 clicks. Keacy Carty leaves. A late wide call is given.
THREE RUNS! Too full and on middle, King flicks it through mid-wicket. Ben Duckett goes behind the ball and flicks it back near the fence.
FOUR! Edged and races away! Brydon Carse offers a bit of width, outside off, it lands and nips in. King looks to cut but outside edges it well past third man for a boundary.
Wicket-maiden from Mahmood! Excellent from England so far! Length ball, outside off. Keacy Carty defends it out.
ALMOST! What a delivery! Saqib Mahmood keeps hitting the hard length, this one shoots up, around off. Keacy Carty hops to defend but inside edges and it almost drags back onto the stumps.
On a good length and on middle, Keacy Carty jabs it onto the deck.

OUT! TAKEN! This time Greaves is out! First shot with intent, and he holes out! Touch fuller and outside off. Justin Greaves tries to drive on the up, but he fails to power much, and Harry Brook at mid off walks to his left and takes a dolly. Bright start by England.
Justin Greaves c H Brook b S Mahmood 4 (5b 1x4 0x6)
Tad fuller and shaping onto the batter, on middle and leg. Greaves nudges it onto the leg side.
Short of a length and around off, climbs off the surface. Greaves taps it to point.
BEATEN AGAIN! The ball is doing a bit! Goes a bit fuller and serves it around off, holds its line this time. King looks to drive but misses.
Five dots in a row! Beaten! England already look more consistent than West Indies were! A good length delivery, around off and it shapes away. King looks to push but misses.
Short of a length and around off, King stands tall and slaps but straight to point.
Goes wide of the crease and angles in a full ball, around off. King pushes with soft hands to cover.
Serves it touch fuller and shaping on middle and leg. King flicks it softly to mid-wicket.
Carse hits the deck hard and bowls on middle and leg, zips in as King looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the body.
Wide! Brydon Carse starts with a full ball going down the leg side. King looks to flick but misses.

England strike in the first over, or are they? Greaves thinks it is off the helmet, and he reviews the decision. Short of a length and around off, Greaves takes his eyes off as he looks to pull in from of his head, but seems to edge it to the keeper. Greaves reviews. UltraEdge shows no spike as the ball passes the bat. Good review, and the on-field umpire will have to change their decision.
FOUR! Streaky and Justin Greaves is off the mark now. This is full and around off, Greaves prods to drive but gets an inside edge past the leg pole and to fine leg for a boundary.

THREE RUNS! West Indies are underway! Fuller delivery swinging on middle, King whips it to deep square leg. Adil Rashid runs to his left, very close to the fence, leans and gets a hand on it as he keeps it away from the fence. A run save.
Saqib Mahmood bowls in the driving length, outside off. King drives but straight to cover.
Lovely nut! A good length delivery around off, it lands and shapes in sharply. King is pinged on the pads as he looks to work it away. A huge appeal for LBW but that was going down leg.
Saqib Mahmood starts with a fuller delivery, wide outside off. King leans as he looks to drive but misses it.

FOUR BYES! 400 breached! On a good length and on middle and leg, reverse swing helps it take past Carse's edge and past the keeper, Shai Hope, who somehow failed to grab that one. It races to fine leg. England end with 400 on the board.
Well bowled! A yorker tailing onto the pads. Rashid makes room and digs it out to cover for a single.
Slides it full and onto the batter's leg, bit of reverse swing. Carse looks to flick it away but edges it onto the leg side for one.
DOT! Seales bowls it into the surface on middle, Carse swings his blade wildly but misses.
Touch fuller and shaping on middle, Rashid nudges it to square leg for a single.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! West Indies are ending things well! Shapes across a length ball, outside off, the off-cutter from Seales. Bethell flashes his blade and edges it to the keeper, Shai Hope, who makes no mistake. A fine, fine knock from young Bethell. Jayden Seales gets his fourth wicket.
Jacob Bethell c S Hope b J Seales 82 (53b 8x4 5x6)
From England's point of view, they have wasted this over! Excellent from West Indies though! Short in length and on leg, Carse is cramped for room as he looks to pull but misses.
ANOTHER DOT! Superb from Joseph! Effort delivery as Alzarri Joseph bangs it short and on middle and leg. Carse looks to pull but misses.
Turning out to be a good over for the bowling team! Hard length delivery, outside off, Carse slaps it to deep cover for a brace.
Alzarri Joseph flirts with the tramline, shorter and outside off. Carse slashes his blade and misses.

OUT! TAKEN! Roston Chase takes another excellent catch! He took one earlier in the game as well! Shorter and around off, gets big on Overton, who looks to pull but slices it towards long on. Roston Chase runs back from mid on, dives and takes over his shoulder. Good take.
Jamie Overton c R Chase b A Joseph 1 (3b 0x4 0x6)
Starts with a length ball, outside off, extra bounce. Overton looks to cut but misses it.
FOUR! Delicately played! So, so good! Perfectly placed! Good length ball, wide of off. Bethell hangs back and plays a late cut shot past backward point for a boundary.
Justin Greaves goes very full and on off. Bethell shuffles across and hits hard but straight to the other side onto the stumps. No run.
A length ball, outside off. Overton punches it through covers for a single.
Wide! Serves it full and outside off, well wide. Overton lets it go.

OUT! TAKEN! Something to cheer for the Windies! A wicket at a crucial time! Justin Greaves sticks to the short-stuff, this is on middle, Will Jacks looks to pull but gets hit on the gloves, it balloons up behind to the keeper, Shai Hope, who gets forward to gobble it. Will Jacks has played his part.
Will Jacks c S Hope b J Greaves 39 (24b 5x4 1x6)
A bumper, outside off. Bethell rides the short ball and pulls, top edges it behind the keeper where the fielder from third man runs across and keeps it down to one.
Wide! West Indies are feeling the pressure! Bangs it short but well across and wide of the batter, it is left alone.
FOUR! Luck with Bethell! Pushes it full and outside off, across the batter. Bethell swings hard but outside edges it to third man and it races to the fence. England go past 380.
Should have been a wide! Matthew Forde comes over the wicket and bowls a slower one over the tramline but Jacks steps across and swings but misses. 24 runs off the over.
FOUR! WOW! Will Jacks is taking over the sound station! He is pumped up! A juicy fuller delivery on middle, Will Jacks with the angle whacks it behind square leg for a boundary.
Wide! Just like the previous delivery! Angles away a full ball over the tramline. Left for a wide.
Wide! More pressure! Gets the angle wrong as Forde dishes out a full ball well outside off. Jacks leaves.

FOUR! Matthew Forde wants to hide his face at the moment! 18 runs of the over with two balls to go! In the slot, full and on middle, almost predictable with the side and the field. Will Jacks hangs back and pumps it down the ground for a boundary.
FOUR! Delicious from Jacks! He is making the fielders chase the ball! Very full and slanting on middle, Will Jacks slog-sweeps it to deep mid-wicket, between long on and mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Changes the side but to no avail! More runs! Bowls from around the wicket and looks for the yorker but bowls a full toss. Will Jacks whips it aerially and to square leg where the fielder runs to his right, gets a hand on it but fails to keep it away.
SIX! Will Jacks joins the party! Very full and on middle, in the slot. Will Jacks thumps it straight down the ground and it goes the distance. Pressure straightaway on Forde.
MISSED OUT! Very full, outside off. Bethell looks to drive but misses.

FOUR! England are pushing for 400! Bethell in particular! Serves it on a length and on middle and off. Bethell bends low, opens his stance and reverse paddle-scoops it over third man for four runs. Oh, no! Nothing is going the bowler's way as Jayden Seales has overstepped. Free-hit next.
Wide! Goes across the batter but over the tramline, left alone.
SIX! Takes the aerial route now! He is in an unstoppable mood now! The crowd is loving it. Touch fuller and outside off. Bethell bends his back and smokes it over long off for a six.
FOUR! Threads it through! Wonderful from Bethell! Length and width on offer. Bethell slaps it through mid off and covers, just a small gap available, and he still hits it through for a boundary.
Tails in a low full toss on the pads. Will Jacks flicks it to deep square leg, who runs to his right and keeps it down to one.
BEATEN! Lovely delivery! Short of a length and on middle, a shade of reverse swing. Will Jacks looks to pull but misses, and it goes over the stumps.
On a length and on middle, Will Jacks backs away and dabs it past short third for a couple of runs.
SIX! The fielders are spectators at the moment! Nails this shot! Serves it short and on middle, Bethell gets inside the line and pulls it over mid-wicket for a six.
BEATEN! Much better from Joseph! Good length delivery, outside off, in the channel and Bethell looks to push but misses.
FOUR! FIFTY for Bethell! The young gun steps up for England. His 3rd ODI fifty! Short in length and on middle and leg, Bethell steps across and pulls it through square leg for four.
Will Jacks doing well to give most of the strike to Bethell! Outside off, Will Jacks cuts it through point for one.
Short of a length and on middle, Bethell pulls it to short fine leg for a quick single.
Bethell backs away and Alzarri Joseph pushes it across on a length and outside off. Bethell slashes his blade and misses. Wided!
Width given outside off and Will Jacks slams it through point for a single.

SIX! CLOBBERED! Short-pitched, around middle and leg, Jacob Bethell clears his front leg and pulls this one. Gets it right out of the middle of his bat, and the ball has sailed over the fence for a biggie down to the long on region.
FOUR! Another boundary to Jacob Bethell. Pitched up wide outside off, Jacob Bethell gets right on top of the bounce and drives this all along the carpet and through extra cover for four.
WIDE! On a length, wide outside off. Jacob Bethell leaves it all alone. Wided.
Slower one, on a length around middle and leg, Will Jacks flicks this through mid-wicket for one.
Good length on off, Will Jacks pushes this through cover for one.
Short-pitched, around off, Will Jacks pulls this flat and towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
On a length wide of off, Jacob Bethell drives this to sweeper cover for one.
FOUR! Yorker down the leg, Will Jacks leans on and just flicks this through the gap between the keeper and short fine for four.
1 run.
Good length on off, Will Jacks pushes this away for one to bring Jacob back on strike.
Back of a length around middle and leg, Jacob Bethell pulls this off the sticker off his bat towards mid-wicket for one.

SIX! DISPATCHED FOR SIX! Short-pitched, around middle and leg, Jacob Bethell gets behind it and pulls this. Hits this well, and the ball has sailed beyond the fence for a huge six towards deep square leg. Also, 300 comes up for England.
Good length around off, Will Jacks flicks this through mid-wicket for one. Jacks was looking for two, but he had hit this too well and had to settle for just one.
Good length on leg, Jacob Bethell pushes this back to the bowler for no run.
Good length on middle and leg, Will Jacks nudges this through mid on for one.
On a length around off, Jacob Bethell drives this wide of long off for one.
Short-pitched around middle and off, Will Jacks pulls this flat towards deep mid-wicket for one.
On a length around off, Jacob Bethell drives this to sweeper cover for one.
On a length around off, Will Jacks punches this to sweeper cover for one.
Back of a length on middle and off. Will fends this through mid-wicket for one.
Good length on off, Will Jacks blocks this back to the bowler.
VENOM FROM SEALES! Short-pitched, around off. Will Jacks had no answer to it and did well to let the ball go through.
Short and wide around off, Will Jacks dabs this to backward point for no run.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Jos has to walk back as Matthew Forde holds onto a regulation catch. Short-pitched, around off, Jos Buttler goes for the pull but hits this away from his body. The ball is miscued off the cue end and has travelled to Matthew Forde at the deep mid-wicket fence. Forder runs in from the fence and holds onto this.
Jos Buttler (wk) c M Forde b J Seales 37 (32b 3x4 1x6)
FOUR! Innovation at its best from Buttler. Full and wide outside off, Joe Root shuffles across and goes for the ramp. Connects well and lobs the short fine leg fielder for a boundary.
Good length outside off, Jacob Bethell goes for the drive but misses.
Good length on off, Jacob Bethell looks to drive this past cover but hits this off the inside towards short cover.
On a length, angling across the batter. Jacob Bethell goes for the cut off his back foot but misses.
Back of a length, nipping back in on off. Jos Buttler pushes this through mid off and takes one.
On a length around off, Jos Buttler pushes this towards mid off for no run.
Short and wide outside off, Jos cuts this to point for no run.
Too full on middle and off, Jos Buttler milks this in the gap for one more.
Pushed through on the pads, Jacob Bethell looks to flick this but gets a top edge through point for one.

SIX! DISPATCHED! Too full, on middle and leg, Jacob Bethell gets down on a knee and slog sweeps this. The ball has sailed over the fence nd into the stands toward the deep mid-wicket region for a huge six.
Tossed up on middle and off, Jacob Bethell plays the reverse and lobs short third for a couple.
Quicker one, on the pads. Jos Buttler tucks this uppish, but wide of the fielder at short mid-wicket for one.
Drilled down to long on for a single.
Back of a length on middle and leg, Jos Buttler tucks this towards short leg for no run.
FOUR! A boundary to follow the biggie. Short pitched on middle and off, Jos Buttler lofts this over the bowler and with mid off inside the circle, the ball has raced away to the fence for four.
SIX! Thumped down the ground for six. On a length wide outside off, Jos Buttler shimmies down the track and has hammered this up and over the fence towards long off for a biggie.
Full and wide outside off, Jacob Bethell guides this to deep third for one.
Slower one, on a good length, wide outside off. Jacob Bethell looks to cut this one but gets beaten on the outside.
Good length wide outside off, Jos Buttler punches this to sweeper cover for a single.
WIDE! On a length wide down the leg, Jos Buttler goes for the flick but misses. Wided.
Back of a length and outside off, there is a hint of outswing, Jacob Bethell looks to defend it but gets squared up and gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! A bouncer and into the body of the batter, Jacob Bethell swivels and looks to hook it. The ball takes the outer edge of the bat and hits his helmet before going to deep fine leg for a boundary.

An off-cutter, on a length and around off, Jacob Bethell adjusts his shot as he uses his feet and plays it off the outer half of the bat. The ball goes to the left of the keeper, who makes a good stop there.
OUCH! Back of a length and around middle, Jacob Bethell swivels on his toes and looks to pull it, but misses and gets hit on his belly.
Slightly fuller and around off, Buttler pushes it towards mid off and takes a quick single.
Good length and around off, Buttler punches it straight to cover.

Short again and around off, Jos Buttler plays it with soft hands and runs the first one very quickly. He wants to have another, but the fielder is quick there to collect the ball and throws it to the keeper to keep the batter to just a single.
Short and around off, Bethell cuts it through covers for a run.
Tempting length and around off, Buttler plays it off the back foot and knocks it down to long on for one. Also, 250 is up for England.
Drags his length back and bowls it around off, Jacob Bethell goes back and uses his wrists to turn it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Tossed it up and around off, Bethell comes forward and blocks it off.
Drops it a bit short and around off, Jos Buttler goes back and punches it to long on for a single.
On a good length and around off, Buttler cuts it through covers for a single.
Hard length and on the top of off stump, Bethell waits and runs it down to deep third for one.
Short of a length and outside off, Jacob Bethell watches it carefully and decides not to offer any shot.
Nagging length and into the stumps, Bethell shows the full face of the bat to defend it.
Back of a length and around middle, Jacob Bethell goes back and pulls it. The ball gets big on him and he mistimes it but gets enough to clear the infield towards mid-wicket and gets two runs.
A slower full ball and around middle, Buttler leans and flicks it to the right of mid on for a quick single.
Short and around middle, Buttler flicks it to deep square leg for one more.
Drifting it on a length and around off, Buttler defends it.
Short and around off, Jacob goes back and punches it to long on for a single.
Dragged length and on the pads, Bethell clips it to short fine leg.
Floated it up and around middle, Jacob Bethell comes forward and defends it right under his eyes.
Tossed it up and around middle, Jacob blocks it off.
FOUR! A LUCKY ONE! On a good length and around off, seems to be a slower one, Jos Buttler looks to cut it but gets an inside edge, and the ball goes past the diving keeper to his left for a boundary.
Dragged length and around off, Jos Buttler pushes it towards mid off and wants a quick single but is sent back by his partner.
On a length and around off, Jacob Bethell tickles it to deep fine leg for a single.
FOUR! DEFT TOUCH! Back of a length and around leg, Jacob Bethell gets inside the line and helps on its way to deep fineleg for a boundary.
On a good length and around off, Jacob Bethell blocks it off.
Nagging length and around middle, Jacob Bethell nudges it to square leg.
Leg Bye! Back of a length and around middle, Jacob Bethell misses his flick shot and the ball clips his front pad on its way to deep fine leg. They take a leg bye.
On a good length and around off, Jacob Bethell leaves it.

FIVE LEG BYES! FIVE LEG BYES! Fuller and on the pads, Jos Buttler misses his flick shot, and the ball rolls away beside the pitch towards the leg side after getting deflected off his pads. The batters take a quick leg bye, and in the meantime, the keeper Shai Hope collects the ball and makes a throw to the non-striker's end, but misses, and there is no backup to that throw. The ball goes away to the boundary, and these are just extra runs for England.
Nagging length and around off, Jos drops it down towards cover.
On a length and outside off, Buttler cuts it towards backward point and take a couple of runs. Roston Chase chases it down and cuts it off.
On a good length and around middle, Jos Buttler flicks it towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! West Indies have been exceptional in the field today! Hard length and outside off, Harry Brook throws his hands at it and looks to cut it hard. The ball goes off the outer part of the bat and flat towards deep backward point, where Keacy Carty comes a bit forward and takes this low catch wonderfully with both his hands.
Harry Brook (c) c K Carty b J Seales 58 (45b 5x4 3x6)

FOUR! STREAKY! A slower short ball, around the right shoulder of the batter, Harry Brook gets deceived by the lack of the pace, and he is a tad early in his shot. Gets it off the gloves and the ball goes to the right of the keeper for a boundary.
Good length and outside off, Brook cuts it down but straight to point.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! On a length and around off, Harry Brook stands tall and punches it aerially on the up through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length and angling into the batter, Buttler pulls it down to deep square leg for one.
On a good length and around off, Jos Buttler drops it down to cover.
Shorter and on middle, Jos Buttler pulls it to square leg for a single.
Length and outside off, Harry Brook punches it to cover for a single. First game officially as a captain, and starts the era with a fine fifty!
Matthew Forde bowls short again but removes all the pace off it, around off and Harry Brook looks to ramp it over but misses.
SIX! That was a hit-me ball! Short and sits nicely onto the batter, on the leg side and Harry Brook hoicks it over fine leg for a six.
FOUR! Harry Brook pounces on the freebie! Off-side was in and Harry Brook just gives himself space to open the side up, this is on middle and Harry Brook thumps it through covers for a boundary.
No ball! Short of a length and outside off. Jos Buttler edges it deliberately to third man for one. Also. 200 is up for England. Matthew Forde has overstepped! Free-hit coming up...
A juicy fuller delivery on middle, Harry Brook smashes it down to long on just for one.
A single to end the over as Harry Brook cuts it through third man for a single.
Jos Buttler is underway! On a nagging length, outside off. Jos Buttler, on his toes, drops it to point for one.
Angles this one on the hips. Harry Brook nudges it behind square leg for one.
Similar to the previous delivery! Length and on middle, Harry Brook keeps it out on the deck.
Angles in from wide of the crease, length and on middle, Harry Brook defends on the leg side.
Jayden Seales bowls it on a length and outside off, Harry Brook taps it to point.
Length ball on middle, nice solid block from Jos Buttler to end the over.
Shorter and on middle, Harry Brook pulls it to square leg for a single.
Wide! Slower, short ball down the leg side, it is left alone.

FOUR! Harry Brook keeps the intent going. Twice, he has edged his boundaries. Short in length and outside off, width on offer and Harry Brook uses his feet to cut but outside edges it to third man for four runs.
This is full and on middle and leg. Harry Brook nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tad fuller and tight on middle and off. Harry Brook defends it out.
Good length delivery, outside off. Harry Brook cuts it to point.

OUT! GONE! Root edges it! Joe Root will be disappointed with himself. This was in the driving length, nice width on it as well. Joe Root leans to drive it but gets a thick outside edge to the keeper, where Shai Hope takes it easily. Would time it 9 out of 10 times, but today was the one time he failed. Excellent innings, however, from Joe Root.
Joe Root c S Hope b J Seales 57 (65b 5x4 0x6)
Length ball on middle, Harry Brook tucks it to square leg for a run.
Slants in a length ball on middle, Harry Brook hangs back and defends.
FOUR! MORE RUNS! Edgy but Harry Brook won't mind! Pace-off delivery, length and outside off. Harry Brook looks to cut but bottom edges it well past the keeper and to the third man fence.
Length ball, outside off, Joe Root guides it to third man for a single.

FOUR! Greets Jayden Seales with a boundary! He, too, might change gears with his fifty up! Sublime timing on this one. Angles in a full ball on middle, Joe Root flicks it through mid-wicket, and it races to the fence.
On middle, fuller and Joe Root keeps the strike as he works it to long on.
Fuller ball on middle, Harry Brook plays it to square leg for a single.

SIX! Pressure releasing over for Brook! He usually doesn't play this kind of shot! On a length and on middle, pre-meditated and Harry Brook steps across and scoops it on one knee over fine leg for a biggie.
On a length and on middle, Harry Brook blocks.

SIX! Oh, Hello! The game is back alive again with this shot! Touch fuller and around off, Harry Brook comes down the track and smashes it over long off for a biggie. Almost 50-odd balls from the previous boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Joe Root nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
Wide! Slides it well down the leg side. Joe Root lets it go.
Tossed up on middle, Harry Brook drills it to the left of mid-wicket, who stops with a dive.
Shorter and outside off, Joe Root cuts it to deep point for a single. FIFTY FOR ROOT! Easy as you like. Played with minimum fuss to get to his 42nd ODI FIFTY!
First shot of aggression but that too for just a run. Full and outside off, Harry Brook drives it to deep cover for a single.
On middle, angling from the fuller length. Joe Root tucks it behind square leg for a single.
Tossed up, outside off, turns away. Harry Brook uses his feet and taps it to cover for a run.
Fractionally short and outside off. Joe Root goes back and plays it to cover for one.
Bowls it on a length and on middle, Joe Root strokes it to long on for a single.
One more run as Harry Brook nicely dabs it to third man.
Short of a length and outside off, Joe Root punches it to cover for one. Easy runs for England.
On a good length and on middle, Joe Root turns it to mid-wicket.
This is full and outside off, Harry Brook drives it to the left of extra cover for a sharp single.
Short in length and around off, Joe Root nudges it to mid-wicket for a single.
A single to end the over as Joe Root bunts this to deep square leg.
Very full and on middle, Harry Brook digs it out to long off for a single.
The one that comes with the arm, full and on middle, Harry Brook leans across and blocks.
150 up for England! Flat and outside off, Joe Root punches it to deep cover for a single.
149 up for the English side! Tossed up on middle, Harry Brook turns it to long on for a single.
Slightly short and outside off. Harry Brook slaps it to cover for no run.
Justin Greaves bowls the slower fuller delivery on off, Joe Root nudges it straight to mid-wicket.
Errs in line and drops it onto the pads. Harry Brook tucks it to square leg and walks to the other end.
Tight from Greaves! On a hard length and on middle, Harry Brook solidly defends.
Short in length and outside off, climbs a bit. Joe Root dabs it to third man for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Joe Root punches it back to the bowler.
Slides this one on the pads. Harry Brook flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter and outside off, Harry Brook knocks it to cover and keeps the strike with a run.
Bowls it full and outside off, easy single as Joe Root pushes it to long off.
Too full and angling on middle and leg, Harry Brook plays it to long on for one.
Floats it full and outside off, Harry Brook leans and drives it to cover.
The arm ball, full and around off, Joe Root punches it to cover for one more.
Motie tosses it up on middle, Harry Brook drills it to long on for a single.
Yorker on the pads, Harry Brook flicks this to square leg for one.
On a length around off, Harry Brook flicks this uppish but short of mid-wicket.
Short-pitched, on off, Joe Root runs this down to third man region for one.
On a length around middle and leg, Joe Root punches this to mid on for no run.
Good length on middle and leg, Harry Brook tucks this to fine leg for one.

OUT! A STUNNER FROM CHASE! On a length, angling away from the batter. Ben Duckett takes a short stride out in front and throws his bat at it. The ball flew off the outside edge and was behind Roston Chase at backward point when he timed his jump to perfection and plucked this out of thin air, one-handed.
Ben Duckett c R Chase b J Greaves 60 (48b 6x4 1x6)
Too full on middle and leg, Ben Duckett thumps this to long on for a single.
Tossed up wide of off, Ben Duckett smashes this towards mid off for no run.
Too full on middle and off, Joe Root milks this in the gap towards mid off for one more.
Quicker one on the pads, Ben Duckett flicks this through square leg for one.
Worked in the gap towards deep square leg for one more.
Fuller on the pads, Ben Duckett flicks this to wide long on for a single
Pitched-up around off, Joe Root drives this to cover for no run.
Good length on the pads, Ben Duckett tucks this to deep mid-wicket for one.
LEG BYE! On a length, drifting down the leg. Joe Root steps across and looks for the flick but misses. The ball is clipped off the front pad, towards fine leg and they run a single.
Good length on middle and leg, Joe Root flicks this to mid-wicket for no run.
Good length, around off, Joe Root guides this to backward point for no run.
FOUR! Perfectly driven down the ground for four. Pitched-up wide of off, Joe Root steps across and just times the drive to perfection for a boundary past the bowler and down to long off.
Full and on off, Joe Root pushes this to sweeper cover for one to end a tidy over for West Indies.
Fired in the line of stumps. Joe Root punches this off his back foot for no run.
Darted around off, Joe Root pushes this towards the left of the bowler and Motie does well to keep it down to nothing.
Tossed up on off, Ben pushes this away from the fielder for a single this time.
Too full on middle and leg, Ben Duckett tucks this to mid-wicket for no run.
Fuller on the pads, Ben Duckett flicks this to mid-wicket for no run.
Back of a length around off, Ben Duckett punches this through cover for a single.
Good length on middle and leg, Joe Root nudges this to deep square for one.
Good length on off, Joe Root punches this back to the bowler.
Too full and wide outside off, Ben Duckett thumps this to sweeper cover for one more.
Back of a length around middle and leg, Joe Root flicks this through square leg for one.
On a length wide outside off, Ben Duckett drives this to sweeper cover for one.
Too full on middle and leg, Ben Duckett drills this to long on for one.
Floated on the pads, Joe Root flicks this to deep square for one.
Too full, on the pads. Joe Root flicks this to long leg and turns back for two. Excellent running between the wickets.
Quicker and flatter on the pads, Ben Duckett nudges this through square leg for one.
Short and wide outside off, Joe Root cuts this to sweeper cover for a single. Brings up the 50-run partnership between Root and Ben.
Fuller on middle and off, Joe Root drills this back to the bowler.
FIFTY FOR DUCKETT! Tossed up wide outside off. Ben Duckett drives this past extra cover and takes two to bring up his half-century.
Tossed up, on leg. Joe Root reverse sweep towards deep point for a single.
Pushed through on off, Joe Root hops up with the bounce and punches this to the right of sweeper cover for two.
Quicker one on the pads, Ben tucks this to deep mid-wicket for one.
Short of a length on middle and off, Joe Root flicks this away for one.
Too full for the reverse sweep. Root hits this well but straight at short third.
Good length on off, Joe Root opens the face of his bat, plays this late and runs this down to the third man region for one.
Short-pitched, on middle and leg. Ben Duckett hops up on his toes and nudges this through square leg for a comfortable rotation of strike.
On a length around middle and off, Joe Root tucks this through square leg for one.
On a length around middle and off. Joe Root flicks this towards mid-wicket for no run.
Good length on middle and leg, Joe Root tucks this towards mid-wicket for no run.

FOUR! Easy pickings for Root. Half-volley, on the pads, Joe Root leans onto it and flicks this. The ball flies in the gap between fine leg and deep square. Jewel Andrew gives it a good chase and puts in a dive to his right to field this but fails to protect the boundary. 100 comes up for England.
Fuller on the pads, Joe Root flicks this to long on for a strike rotation.
A top-spinner from Chase, outside Root's off-stump. Joe goes for the punch of his back foot, but the ball shoots on him and Root ends up pushing this to cover.
Quicker and fuller around off, Ben Duckett drills this to long off for a single.
Too full on middle and leg. Root hops back and rolls this to long on for a single.
Pushed through on middle and off, Joe Root pushes this back to the bowler.
FOUR! Another boundary for Root. Tossed up around off, Joe Root picks the length early and goes for the reverse sweep. Plays that well and beats the fielder at short third for a boundary.
Back of a length around off, Joe Root hops back and guides this to the third man region for a single to end the over.
Touch fuller, wide outside off. Joe Root punches this on the front foot but closer to cover for a dot.
Good length on middle and leg, Joe Root defends this one.
Back of a length on the pads, Ben Duckett comes inside the line of it and tucks this to fine leg for one.
On a length, wide outside off. Ben Duckett slashes hard at it but gets beaten on the outside.
Good length on top of off, Ben Duckett defends this off his front foot.
Full and around middle, Root defends it back to the bowler. England are 90/1 after the first Powerplay!
FOUR! CASHED OUT! A low full toss, tries to follow the batter, around leg, Joe Root backs away and swipes it to deep backward square leg for a boundary.
NO BALL! Floated it up and a bit outside off, Ben Duckett pushes it to long off for a single. Uh...Oh! Chase has overstepped, and it is called a No Ball! A free-hit is coming up!
Short and around middle, Root nudges it to deep square leg for a single.

In the air... but falls down! Tossed it up and around off, Ben Duckett goes on his knees and looks to fetch it out with a sweep shot. He mistimes it, and the ball goes in the air towards deep square leg. The fielder in the deep runs in to his right but the swirling ball lands down just right to him. A single taken!
Keeps it shorter and around off, Root stays deep in his crease and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Nagging length and around off, Root goes back and pushes it to cover.

FOUR! INNOVATIVE! Full and around off, seems to be a slower one, Ben Duckett shuffles across the crease and ramps it over the keeper behind the wickets for a boundary. Even the bowler appreciates the shot!
On a good length and around off, Root punches it towards mid off with soft hands and takes a quick single.
Hard length and around off, Root rides the bounce and drops it down towards cover.
Nagging length but on the pads, Root flicks it towards short fine leg, where the fielder makes a fine stop.
BEATEN! A bit fuller and outside off, with a wobbly seam, Joe Root comes to drive it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and around off, Duckett turns it towards square leg for a quick single.
Touch short and around off, Duckett punches it to long off for one more.
SIX! INTO THE STANDS! Slower through the air, full and around middle, Ben Duckett skips down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball, and whips it over the cow corner for a biggie.
Floated it up and around off, Ben Duckett punches it back to the bowler.
Misfield! Dragged length and outside off, Duckett cuts it hard towards extra cover, where Keacy Carty makes a fumble in collecting the ball and it goes off his hands. They take two runs.
Full and around off, Root uses his feet and flicks it to long on for one to get off the mark.
Tossed it up and around off, Ben Duckett knocks it down to long off for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! A fantastic catch has ended the stay of Jamie Smith! That in between length and around off, Smith takes out his front leg forward a bit and looks to heave it across the line to the leg side. He doesn't get the desired elevation and hits it off the inner half of the bat. The ball goes towards mid-wicket, where Brandon King takes it with a reverse cup over his head. The ball was coming with a speed, but King held on to it nicely!
Jamie Smith c B King b A Joseph 37 (24b 7x4 0x6)

Falls down! Short of a length, into the pitch, around middle, Jamie Smith looks to pull it but the ball gets big on him and he mistimes his shot towards mid on. The ball lobs up in the air but falls down ahead of the incoming fielder.

Nagging length and a bit outside off, comes in with the angle, Jamie Smith looks to flick it but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on the back pad. There is an appeal for LBW but is turned down!
On a length and outside off, Duckett runs it down to deep third for one.

FOUR! DEFT TOUCH! Back of a length and around leg, with fine leg inside the circle, a ball to hit away. Ben Duckett swivels on his toes and just gets desired bat on it as he tickles it to the right of short fine leg for a boundary.
Begins with a hard-length ball, and a bit outside off, Ben Duckett hangs back and blocks it off.
FOUR! AND ANOTHER! Jayden Seales overcorrects his length and bowls it much fuller and on the pads, Jamie Smith leans on and flicks it to mid-wicket for another boundary.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Hard length and outside off, Jamie Smith cashes on the width offered as he stands tall and cuts it through cover point for a boundary.

Back of a length and angling into the body of the batter, Smith goes back and half-pulls it. He hasn't middle it but gets enough to clear the mid-wicket fielder and they take two runs. Also, 50 comes up for England!
Goes fuller and a bit outside off, Jamie Smith pushes it back to the bowler, who fumbles in trying to stop the ball. It rolls away towards mid off off the hands of Seales.
Nagging length and outside off, Smith drops it down to mid-wicket.

Excellent running between the wickets! On a good length and outside off, Duckett waits for it and opens bat face very late. He guides it towards deep backward point where the deep point fielder runs in to his right and puts in a dive to cut it off. But the ball parries away to his right off his hand and the batter take three runs after seeing an opportunity.
FOUR! GLORIOUS! Hard length and around off, Jamie Smith shifts his weight to the back foot and punches it. He finds the gap at extra covers for a boundary. England are 46/0 after five overs.
Full and around middle, Jamie flicks it but straight to mid-wicket this time.
Easy peasy! On the pads and a tad fuller, Smith takes out a step forward, gets to the pitch of the ball, and flicks it through the gap at mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
FOUR! AGGRESSIVE! Full and around off, Jamie Smith takes the charge, comes down the wicket, and lofts it over mid off for a cracking boundary. England off to a flier here!
Back of a length and around off, Jamie Smith presses back and opens his bat face off late. He guides it in the gap between backward point and cover point for a couple of runs.
Nagging length and around off, Jamie Smith pushes it towards cover.

FOUR! GOOD USE OF THE WRISTS! On a length and around middle, Ben Duckett leans on a bit and uses his wrists to flick it through the big gap at mid-wicket. The deep square leg fielder runs in to his right to cut it off, but the ball wins the race.
Back of a length and around off, Smith swings hard at it but gets it off the inner half of the bat to the right of mid on. They take a quick single.
A bit fuller and around off, Ducektt plays out this with open bat face to deep point for a single.
Tempting length and outside off, Duckett hits it hard but straight to the cover fielder.
Dragged length and well outside off, Ben looks to cut it but gets an underedge off the cue end of the bat back to the keeper behind the wickets. Good stop there!
FOUR! FLICKED AWAY! Touch fuller and on the pads, Ben Duckett comes forward a bit and whips it away through mid-wicket for a boundary. Right off the middle of the bat!
Hard length and around off, Jamie Smith takes a step forward, gets to the pitch of the ball, and drops it down towards extra cover.
On the pads and on the fuller length, Duckett flicks it to deep fine leg for a single.
Nagging length and outside off, Ben Duckett gets inside the line and shoulders his arms to let it go.

FOUR! THRASHED! On a good length but well outside off, offers width to the batter. Ben Duckett stands tall and reaches out to cut it through the cover point region for a boundary. Nice timing on that one!
On a length and around off, Jamie Smith flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Back of a length and around the hips of the batter, Duckett helps on its way to deep fine leg for a single.
FOUR! WOW! On the other side! Much fuller and on the pads, easy for Jamie Smith as he leans on and flicks it in the gap through mid-wicket for another boundary.
FOUR! CLASS ACT! A bit fuller and outside off, Jamie Smith pouches on it with his stride forward and crunches it through covers for a boundary.

There is a loud appeal for LBW, but the umpire shakes his head again! West Indies have gone upstairs this time! Touch fuller and around middle, seaming in, Jamie Smith looks to flick it, but his head falls over and he misses the line and gets hit on the front pad. The third umpire comes into play and there is nothing on UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking shows that it will miss the leg stump. WI lose a review here!

DROPPED AND FOUR! On a good length and outside off, there is an outward movement. Jamie Smith throws his hands at it with no feet movement and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies to the right of the second slip, where Justin Greaves throws himself in the air with his extended right arm, but the ball goes through his hands for a boundary at third man.
Hits the deck hard this time, on a length and around off, Smith blocks it off.

Massive appeal for LBW but is turned down by the umpire! Starts off with a yorker, right on the money, but the ball swings back in the air. Jamie Smith looks to jam it out but plays the wrong line and gets pinged on the front pad. Probably, it is going down leg.
Dragged length and outside off, Ben Duckett looks to run it down towards third man but misses.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Over-pitched, and a bit outside off, Ben Duckett takes a step forward to negotiate the swing and creams the drive through the gap at covers for a boundary. First of the day!
Play and a miss! Fuller again and outside off, swings away after pitching a bit, Ben Duckett throws his hands at it and looks to drives it on the up but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Pitched it up and around off, Ben looks to drive it down the ground but gets a leading edge off the outer half of the bat towards cover.
From around the wicket, full and a bit outside off, Ben Duckett watches it carefully and leaves it.

England and Jamie Smith are underway straightaway! Forde begins with a full ball, a hint of swing away, around off, Smith comes forward to play out to the off side but gets a thick inside edge that goes to deep square leg for a single.
